vel":"Unit","justification":"This is pre-dispatch construction policy logic ('before dispatch'), so failures are in local budgeting/truncation/rejection algorithm, not external interaction. Rejected Integration/System: behavior text does not require actual send or network effects.","test_description":"Test request-builder/token-budget function with inputs above and below budget and assert policy outcome (truncate or reject) and computed token count respect configured limit before any client call.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.82,"Integration":0.16,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Provider-reported token usage for a typical document stays within the configured per-call budget.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Must observe real provider-reported usage; mocked usage can always be made compliant and would hide true over-budget failures. Because this executes a real AI API call and usage can depend on actual model completion behavior, minimum boundary is Agentic (not just local wiring). Rejected Workflow: single call/decision, no multi-step agent chain.","test_description":"Execute real classification calls for representative 'typical' documents with configured budget; assert provider usage metadata (prompt/completion/total per provider schema) is <= budget threshold for each call, with retry-independent accounting.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.33,"Agentic":0.65,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When the API signals that the request rate is too high, the module waits and retries rather than returning an error to the caller.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears in orchestration between retry policy, timing/backoff, and API client error mapping. In-process stub can reproduce 429/rate-limit signal and verify retry path; real network/OS is 